</ul>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Stone_(unit)&action=edit&section=6.php.html" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="reflist" style="list-style-type: decimal;">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Since the <a href="International_yard_and_pound" title="International yard and pound">international yard and pound</a> agreement of 1 July 1959, the <a href="Pound_(mass)#Current_use" title="Pound (mass)">international avoirdupois pound</a> has been defined as exactly <span style="white-space:nowrap">0.453<span style="margin-left:.25em">5</span>92<span style="margin-left:.25em">3</span>7&#160;kg</span><sup id="cite_ref-Standards1959_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Standards1959-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> giving a stone of exactly <span style="white-space:nowrap">6.350<span style="margin-left:.25em">2</span>93<span style="margin-left:.25em">1</span>8&#160;kg</span>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-39"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-39">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">In modern colloquial Dutch, a <i>pond</i> is used as an alternative for 500&#160;g, not 1&#160;kg.</span></li>
</ol>
</div>
